@page "/rendermode/interactive"
@rendermode InteractiveServer

<PageTitle>Interactive Counter Example</PageTitle>

<h1>Interactive Counter Example</h1>

<div class="alert alert-success" role="alert">
    <strong>âœ… Interactive:</strong> This counter works because the component is rendered interactively on the server.
</div>

<p>To enable this, the following directive is added to the top of the file. This tells Blazor to establish a connection to handle UI events.</p>

<div class="card bg-light mb-3">
    <div class="card-body">
        <code>@@rendermode InteractiveServer</code>
    </div>
</div>

<p>Try clicking the button below - notice that the count updates immediately:</p>
<code>Current count: @@currentCount</code>

<button class="btn btn-success" @onclick="IncrementCount">Click me (works!)</button>

<div class="mt-3">
    <p><strong>Why does it work?</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Interactive server rendering maintains a connection to the server</li>
        <li>JavaScript enables real-time UI updates</li>
        <li>Event handlers like @@onclick are fully functional</li>
        <li>Changes are processed on the server and sent to the browser instantly</li>
    </ul>
</div>

@code {
    private int currentCount = 0;

    private void IncrementCount()
    {
        currentCount++;
    }
} 